# Line-ending policy. CRITICAL part: shell/SLURM scripts MUST stay LF --
# with core.autocrlf=true on Windows, `git archive` (the deployment tarball)
# otherwise exports them with CRLF, which breaks `source` and sbatch on the
# Linux node ("Batch script contains DOS line breaks"). Caught 2026-07-02.
*.sh     text eol=lf
*.slurm  text eol=lf

# Everything else: normalized in the repo (LF blobs), platform-native in
# Windows working trees. MATLAB / nvcc / compilers accept either ending.
*.m      text
*.cu     text
*.cpp    text
*.c      text
*.h      text
*.md     text

# Binary artefacts (never normalize).
*.mat    binary
*.png    binary
*.mexw64 binary
*.mexa64 binary
